 fincera inc formerly autochina international ltd incorporated on october   focuses on providing webbased financing and ecommerce services for small and mediumsized businesses smbs and individuals in china the companys operations consist of two operating segments the internetbased business and property lease and management business the company is focused principally on its commercial vehicle sales leasing and support business which provides commercial vehicle leasing solutions for smbs in chinas transportation industry the company has targeted the transportation industry for its internetbased products which are ceravest cerapay and truship the company classifies its internetbased businesses into three categories financial services payment and settlement and ecommerceinternetbased businessesceravest is the companys peertopeer pp lending platform through which the company offers smbs shortterm sixmonth financing the platforms website is wwwqingyidaicom its loans are funded through ceravest investors which can invest in notes through the ceravest platform and by the company for any remaining unfunded portion ceravest loans bear interest at approximately  per annum the loan is guaranteed by the smbs and over  of the loan is remitted to the company as a security deposit the company also offers the ceravest flex product ceravest flex allows investors to add or withdraw funds as they please it transfers the underlying assets which are cerapay receivables to investors through a transfer agreement at a quoted rate of approximately  per annum the transferred notes have no specific lending period or maturity datethe company adjusts the size of the underlying pool of cerapay receivables according to the total amount of investment in ceravest flex all of the foregoing is reflected in the applicable transfer agreements no clauses in the ceravest transfer agreements require the company to repurchase any default loans however the company voluntarily commits to assist the investors to eliminate investment risks and retain the principal and the stated interest the company also voluntarily commits to repurchasing notes from investors that would like to withdraw their funds prior to loan maturity after which the company then relists these repurchased loans for sale to other investors all investments received are secured by the same amount of the counterpart loans net and other financing receivables the company is due from the borrowers and the cerapay users respectively the company generates revenue from ceravest primarily by charging origination fees and from interest on the loans the company makecerapay is the companys online payments platform that operates on its own closedloop network the platforms website is wwwdianfubaocom cerapay users are provided with a credit line that can be utilized at participating cerapay merchants or be used to pay other cerapay users having features similar to a credit card there are no fees other than late fees and penalties for cerapay users that become delinquent on amounts borrowed for using the cerapay payments service as long as any outstanding balances are paid in full each month the company generates revenue from cerapay primarily by charging transaction fees merchants can use cerapay funds to make payments to other cerapay users or merchants or cash out the funds through transfer to a bank account cerapay users are subject to an application and credit approval process and provide guarantees and collateral which can include a commercial vehicle a security deposit or real estate before they are provided with a credit line cerapay in conjunction with its third party payment partners serves as the online payment method for all of its ecommerce platformstruship is the companys online ecommerce platform whereby trucking industry merchants such as dealerships and leasing companies can establish an online storefront and conduct sales transactions through cerapay the platforms website is wwwchecom the truship logistics shipping marketplace is launched on the platform it allows participants in chinas fragmented longhaul trucking industry to publish browse and connect on shipping jobs across the country payment transactions resulting from connections made on truship logistics can be completed with cerapay and the subsequent data is used as underwriting metrics for ceravest loans to small businesses the company also operates a network of branch offices in over  provinces municipalities and autonomous regions across china these branches support local sales staff for its internetbased businessesproperty lease and management businessthe company owns and leases out office space in the kai yuan finance center which is an approximately story largescale commercial building with hotel office and ancillary facilities erected on a land parcel with a site area of approximately  square meters in the central business district of shijiazhuang china the company owns floors  to  and  to  which comprise a total gross floor area of approximately  square meters its corporate headquarters occupy floors  and  and the company leases out the space that the company does not occupy approximately  square meters » full overview of autcfpk company address fincera inc kai yuan centerth floor  east main streetshijiazhuang   heb    p f  company web links home page officers  directors name compensation yong hui li  chialun wang  xing wei  lei chen  spencer ang li  » more officers  directors fincera inc news » more autcfpk news related topics stocksstock screenerfinancialscorporate financial services fincera inc autcfqbb profile  ftcom subscribe sign in menu search financial times myft search the ft search search the ft search close marketsmarkets dataequities financial timesclosesearch theftsearch equities fincera incautcfqbbselect symbolunited statesautcfqbbotcqbfincera incactionsadd to watchlistadd to portfolioadd an alertconsumer servicesgeneral retailersprice usdtodays change  shares traded year changebet